      "role": "user",
      "content": "wait, so you're basically saying the economic concerns are just a secondary issue compared to the moral one? if the data shows it works better and it's the more compassionate path, isn't it kind of a settled debate at that point? it feels like you're agreeing that the \"efficiency\" argument is just a way to avoid the actual human cost.",
